<td style="text-align:left"><em>Node.js only--not available in browser.</em> Dictionary of headers to be sent with the initial connection to the server.  In server code, these can be accessed via <code>req.socket.handshake.headers</code> in controller actions or <code>socket.handshake.headers</code> in <a href="/documentation/reference/configuration/sails-config-sockets">socket lifecycle callbacks</a>.  This is useful for (for example) sending a <code>cookie</code> header with the initial handshake, allowing a socket to connect to a previously-established Sails session.</td>
